            <thetext>Let&#39;s say we have a disabled textfield widget and it has a tooltip.

textfield.setToolTipText(&quot;I&#39;m a tooltip.&quot;);
textfield.setEnabled(false);

In this case the tooltip is shown, even if the textfield is disabled. The normal behavior is to not show the tooltip of disabled widgets. 



To clarify why I think this is a normal behavior, let&#39;s see how the normal input tag behaves in a HTML page:

&lt;input id=&quot;textfield&quot; type=&quot;text&quot; title=&quot;this is a tooltip&quot;/&gt;

If we hover over it, the title is shown like a tooltip in all browsers. If we disable the input:

&lt;input id=&quot;textfield&quot; type=&quot;text&quot; title=&quot;this is a tooltip&quot; disabled=&quot;disabled&quot;/&gt;

the tooltip doesn&#39;t show up anymore.</thetext>
